Consider a class Apple which is extended by class Banana. Class Apple contains a single integer member 'number_of_items'.
Class Banana contains an integer member 'number_of_items', a constructor and a member method show() which displays the values of member variable 'number_of_items' of class Apple and class Banana respectively .

Complete the missing code to assign the values entered by the user to the member variable 'number_of_items' of the apple class and the banana class respectively. Display them using the show() method as shown below.

Enter the number of apples:
1
Enter the number of bananas:
3
Number of apples:1
Number of bananas:3